speech.p:
May I point out, Major Milner, that the Clause reads:
(1) Where any person is elected to any of the following offices, that is to say—


(a) chairman of a county council, county alderman or county councillor;

(b) mayor, alderman or councillor of a borough;

(c) chairman of a district council or district councillor."

There are many hon. Members who feel that when a person is elected to such an office, he should be given an opportunity of returning to this country in order to serve on the local authority to which he has been appointed, and that a provision should be inserted to that effect. We consider that this Clause should be amended to deal with that. I had expected that on this Clause the Minister would say something on that matter, which was raised in the Second Reading Debate.
